Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Keep the @unsalted butter{20%g} in the fridge.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 3cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer. TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf for ~{20%minutes} - you'll roast them for longer once you've crushed them.

Meanwhile, finely chop the @chives{1}(finely chopped) (use scissors if easier). Trim the @green beans{150%g}.

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Cut one half of the @lemon{1}(cut into slices) into slices.

Lay the @salmon fillets{2}, skin-side down, onto a lined baking tray. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then lay lemon slices on top.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

When the potatoes have cooked for ~{20%minutes}, remove them from the oven.

Use the bottom of a #bowl{} or pan to lightly crush each potato.

Drizzle the smashed potatoes with more @oil{}, then return to the top shelf of your oven to roast until crispy and golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Roast the salmon on the middle shelf until cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The salmon is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the green beans and stir-fry until starting to char, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in half the garlic, then turn the heat down to medium and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add a splash of @water{for the green beans} and immediately cover with a #lid{} or some @foil{}. Cook until the beans are tender, ~{4-5%minutes}, then transfer to a bowl and cover to keep warm.

Pop the pan back on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Add the remaining garlic and stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @water{50%ml}(for the sauce) and @vegetable stock paste{10%g}. Bring to the boil and boil for ~{1%minute}.

Turn the heat down to low and whisk in the cold butter until melted and the sauce has thickened. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

When everything's ready, share your ultimate roasted salmon and veg between your plates.

Stir the chives into the butter sauce, then spoon over the fish to finish.

Enjoy!